<subsection xml:id="subsec-surface-area-of-a-cone">
    <title>Surface area of a cone</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-surface-area-of-a-cone">
        <statement>
            <p>
                A <m>\textbf{cone}</m> is a pyramid with a circular
                base.
            </p>
            <p>
                A cone consists of a circular base and a curved surface that connects the base to the apex (the tip of the cone).
            </p>
            <p>
                The <m>\textbf{slant height}</m> of a cone is the distance from the apex to any point on the edge of the base.
            </p>
            
        </statement>
    </definition>
